GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 3
HOUSE BILL 3
Committee Substitute Favorable 3/4/25
Senate Elections Committee Substitute Adopted 6/11/25
Short Title: Various Local Election Changes II. (Local)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
January 30, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MODIFY THE PROCESS FOR FILLING VACANCIES ON THE CABARRUS
3 COUNTY BOARD OF COMMISSIONERS; TO PROVIDE FOR THE PARTISAN
4 ELECTION FOR MEMBERS OF THE CURRITUCK COUNTY BOARD OF
5 EDUCATION, SUBJECT TO A REFERENDUM; TO PROVIDE FOR THE PARTISAN
6 ELECTION FOR MEMBERS OF THE PITT COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION; TO
7 REQUIRE REGULAR MUNICIPAL ELECTIONS IN ALL OF THE MUNICIPALITIES
8 IN PAMLICO COUNTY TO BE HELD IN EVEN-NUMBERED YEARS; TO REQUIRE
9 REGULAR MUNICIPAL ELECTIONS IN THE VILLAGE OF SIMPSON TO BE HELD
10 IN EVEN-NUMBERED YEARS; AND TO REQUIRE THAT MUNICIPAL ELECTIONS
11 IN THE CITY OF MONROE BE CONDUCTED ON A PARTISAN BASIS.
12 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
13
14 PART I. CABARRUS COUNTY BOARD OF COMMISSIONERS VACANCIES
15 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 153A-27.1(h), as amended by S.L. 2025-3, reads as rewritten:
16 "(h) This section shall apply only in the following counties: Alamance, Alexander,
17 Alleghany, Avery, Beaufort, Brunswick, Buncombe, Cabarrus, Caldwell, Carteret, Caswell,
18 Cherokee, Clay, Cleveland, Cumberland, Dare, Davidson, Davie, Forsyth, Graham, Guilford,
19 Harnett, Haywood, Henderson, Hyde, Jackson, Lee, Lincoln, Macon, Madison, McDowell,
20 Mecklenburg, Moore, Onslow, Pender, Polk, Randolph, Rockingham, Rutherford, Sampson,
21 Stanly, Stokes, Transylvania, and Yancey."
22 SECTION 1.(b) This section applies to Cabarrus County only.
23 SECTION 1.(c) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
24 vacancies filled on or after that date.
