28 CURRITUCK COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION
29 SECTION 2.(a) Section 1 of Chapter 96 of the 1963 Session Laws reads as rewritten:
30 "Section 1. (a) The Board of Education of Currituck County shall consist of five members to
31 be elected by the electors of said county as hereinafter set out.serve staggered four-year terms.
32 (b) At the general election to be held in said county in 1964, there shall be elected one
33 Four members of the Board of Education of Currituck County shall be elected from residency
34 districts and one member shall be elected from the county at-large. For the four residency
35 districts, no person shall be eligible to file for or be elected to the board of education unless the
*H3-v-3*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 person is a qualified voter and resident of the residency district in which the candidate seeks to
2 be elected. One member of the Board of Education of Currituck County shall be elected from
3 each of the following residency districts:
4 (1) Moyock Township and Township.
5 (2) one member from Fruitful Township who shall serve for terms of four (4)
6 years each. Fruitville Township.
7 (3) At said election there shall be elected one member of the Board from Poplar
8 Branch and one member from Township Township.
9 (4) Crawford Township who shall serve for terms of two (2) years each. At said
10 election there shall be elected one member of the board from the county at
11 large who shall serve for a term of two (2) years. Thereafter, as the terms of
12 office of the members expire, their successors shall be elected and shall serve
13 for terms of four (4) years each and until their successors are elected and
14 qualified.Township.
15 At all elections held for election of members of the board of education of said county, the
16 candidates shall be elected by the voters of the county voting as a whole.
17 (c) Notwithstanding G.S. 115C-37, members of the Board of Education of Currituck
18 County shall be elected on a partisan basis at the time of the general election in each
19 even-numbered year as terms expire. Candidates for election to the Board of Education of
20 Currituck County shall be nominated at the same time and in the same manner as other county
21 officers. Members shall take office on the first Monday in December following their election.
22 Members shall serve until their successors are elected and qualified. Except as otherwise
23 provided, elections shall be conducted in accordance with Chapters 115C and 163 of the General
24 Statutes.
25 (d) All vacancies on the membership of the Board of Education of Currituck County by
26 death, resignation, or other causes shall be filled in accordance with G.S. 115C-37.1."
27 SECTION 2.(b) This section does not affect the terms of office of any person elected
28 in 2024 to the Board of Education of Currituck County. Any vacancy on the Board of Education
29 of Currituck County for a member elected in 2024 shall be filled by appointment by the remaining
30 members of the Board of Education of Currituck County to serve the remainder of the unexpired
31 term. When a vacancy occurs in a seat elected from a residency district, the successor shall be
32 elected from the residency district of the vacating member. Each member of the Board of
33 Education of Currituck County elected in 2024, or any member appointed to fill a vacancy for a
34 member elected in 2024, shall serve until a successor has been elected and qualified.
35 SECTION 2.(c) G.S. 115C-37.1(d), as amended by S.L. 2025-3, reads as rewritten:
36 "(d) This section shall apply only to the Hickory City Board of Education and the
37 Newton-Conover City Board of Education and in the following counties: Alexander, Alleghany,
38 Ashe, Beaufort, Brunswick, Burke, Cabarrus, Caldwell, Carteret, Catawba, Cherokee, Clay,
39 Craven, Currituck, Dare, Davie, Forsyth, Graham, Harnett, Henderson, Hyde, Iredell, Lee,
40 Lincoln, Madison, McDowell, Mitchell, New Hanover, Onslow, Pamlico, Pender, Polk, Rowan,
41 Rutherford, Stanly, Stokes, Surry, Vance, Washington, and Yancey."
42 SECTION 2.(d) The question of changing the method of election for the members
43 of the Board of Education of Currituck County shall be submitted to the qualified voters of
44 Currituck County at the general election to be held on November 3, 2026, which election shall
45 be conducted in accordance with the laws governing elections at that time. The question to be
46 used in the voting systems and ballots shall be:
47 "[ ] FOR [ ] AGAINST
48 Changing the method of election for the members of the Board of Education of
49 Currituck County from nonpartisan to partisan."
50 SECTION 2.(e) The Currituck County Board of Elections shall certify the results of
51 the referendum conducted under subsection (d) of this section. If the certification from the
Page 2 House Bill 3-Third Edition

