8 PITT COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION
9 SECTION 2.1.(a) Section 1 of Chapter 193 of the 1987 Session Laws, as amended
10 by S.L. 2013-318, reads as rewritten:
11 "Section 1. Beginning in December 2014, the The Pitt County Board of Education shall
12 consist of nine members. Nine members shall be elected from single-member districts, as
13 described in Section 5. Only voters residing in the district may vote for the member from that
14 district."
15 SECTION 2.1.(b) Section 4 of Chapter 193 of the 1987 Session Laws, as amended
16 by S.L. 2013-318, reads as rewritten:
17 "Sec. 4. Elections shall be held on a partisan basis in even-numbered years as terms expire,
18 at the time of the regular election of general election. Candidates for election to the Pitt County
19 Board of Education shall be nominated at the same time and manner as other county officers.
20 Members shall take office at the time set by general State law on the first Monday in December
21 following the election and shall serve for staggered terms of four years. Members shall serve
22 until a successor has been elected and qualified. Except as otherwise provided, the election shall
23 be conducted in accordance with Chapters 115C and 163 of the General Statutes."
24 SECTION 2.1.(c) Section 6 of Chapter 193 of the 1987 Session Laws reads as
25 rewritten:
26 "Sec. 6. Vacancies on the Pitt County Board of Education shall be filled by appointment by
27 the remaining members of the Board. The person appointed shall serve until the next regularly
28 scheduled election for county boards of education, at which time a person shall be elected to fill
29 the remainder of the unexpired term or, if the term is due to expire that year, a new term. The
30 person appointed to fill a vacancy must reside in the same district as the departing member.in
31 accordance with G.S. 115C-37.1."
32 SECTION 2.1.(d) This section does not affect the term of office of any member
33 elected in 2024 to the Pitt County Board of Education. Any vacancy on the Pitt County Board of
34 Education for a member elected in 2024 shall be filled by appointment by the remaining members
35 of the Pitt County Board of Education to serve the remainder of the unexpired term. Each member
36 of the Pitt County Board of Education elected in 2024, or any member appointed to fill a vacancy
37 in 2024, shall serve until a successor has been elected and qualified.
38 SECTION 2.1.(e) G.S. 115C-37.1(d), as amended by S.L. 2025-3, reads as rewritten:
39 "(d) This section shall apply only to the Hickory City Board of Education and the
40 Newton-Conover City Board of Education and in the following counties: Alleghany, Ashe,
41 Beaufort, Brunswick, Burke, Cabarrus, Caldwell, Carteret, Catawba, Cherokee, Clay, Craven,
42 Dare, Davie, Forsyth, Graham, Harnett, Henderson, Hyde, Iredell, Lee, Lincoln, Madison,
43 McDowell, Mitchell, New Hanover, Onslow, Pamlico, Pender, Pitt, Polk, Rutherford, Stanly,
44 Stokes, Surry, Vance, Washington, and Yancey."
45 SECTION 2.1.(f) This section becomes effective the first Monday in December
46 2026, and elections in 2026 and thereafter shall be conducted accordingly.
