1 SECTION 3.(a) Section 8 of the Charter of the Town of Alliance, being Chapter 760
2 of the 1965 Session Laws, reads as rewritten:
3 "Sec. 8. Mayor and Mayor Pro Tem. At its organizational meeting on the first Saturday in
4 July, 1967, and biennially thereafter following a each regular municipal election, the board of
5 commissioners shall elect the town commissioner with the largest vote at said election, as
6 chairman, chair, who shall act as mayor, and another of its members its vice chairman, chair, who
7 shall act as mayor pro tempore. The mayor shall preside at meetings of the governing board, and
8 shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as are or may be conferred and
9 imposed upon him or her by the general laws of North Carolina, by this Charter, and by the
10 ordinances of the town. He The mayor shall be recognized as the head of the town government,
11 for all ceremonial purposes, by the courts for the service of all legal process in civil matters, and
12 by the Governor for the purposes of civil defense and military law. In time of public danger or
13 emergency the mayor shall, if so authorized and directed by the town governing board, take and
14 exercise command of the town police, maintain order, and enforce the law. In case of the absence
15 or other disability of the mayor to act, the mayor pro tempore shall act as mayor during the
16 continuance of the absence or other disability."
17 SECTION 3.(b) Section 14 of the Charter of the Town of Alliance, being Chapter
18 760 of the 1965 Session Laws, reads as rewritten:
19 "Sec. 14. Municipal Elections. The regular election of members of the board of
20 commissioners shall be held on the last Saturday in June in the odd-numbered years, beginning
21 with the last Saturday in June, 1967, and biennially thereafter. The board of commissioners may,
22 for any other lawful purpose, and by resolution, order a special election, fix the time for holding
23 the same, and provide all other details and means for holding such special election.at the time of
24 the general election in each even-numbered year. The board of commissioners shall be elected
25 on a nonpartisan plurality basis and the results determined in accordance with G.S. 163-292."
26 SECTION 3.(c) Section 15 of the Charter of the Town of Alliance, being Chapter
27 760 of the 1965 Session Laws, reads as rewritten:
28 "Sec. 15. Regulations of Elections. All elections shall be conducted in accordance with the
29 general uniform municipal laws relating to municipal elections, in Chapter 163 of the General
30 Statutes, except as otherwise provided herein."
31 SECTION 3.(d) Sections 16, 17, 18, and 19 of the Charter of the Town of Alliance,
32 being Chapter 760 of the 1965 Session Laws, are repealed.
33 SECTION 3.(e) No municipal elections shall be conducted in the Town of Alliance
34 in 2025. The terms of office of the five members of the board of commissioners serving on the
35 effective date of this section whose terms are set to expire in 2025 shall be extended by one year.
36 Regular municipal elections shall be conducted in the Town of Alliance in even-numbered years
37 beginning in 2026.
